  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: b583188ac94622b4cb532c86de32db8d, type: 3}
  m_Name: ExampleA
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  data:
    title: Quick Start to Documentation
    documentation: 'Hi! This is a shortdemo on how to use the in-editor documentation
      system.


      <img src="Assets/ExternalPlugins/EditorDocumentation/Examples/Images/Talalalala.jpg"
      height=200>


      The following system supports Rich text formatting. This
      includes:


      - <b> Bold text </b>

      - <color=cyan> Colored text </color>

      - 
      <size=25>Font sizes</size>

      -  <size=25><color=red>Multiple tags</color></size>


      and
      as you saw, Images.



      <b><size=30>How to Document</size></b>


      In
      the inspector, create a <color=cyan>documentation scriptable object</color>,
      like the one you''re using to read the following text right now.


      <img
      src="Assets/ExternalPlugins/EditorDocumentation/Examples/Images/documentationInspectorWindow.png"
      height=400>


      Edit the documentation scriptable object as you please
      to add the necessary data.



      Once completed, in your relevant scripts,
      create an <color=cyan>InspectorDocumentation</color> variable.


      <img
      src="Assets/ExternalPlugins/EditorDocumentation/Examples/Images/documentationInspectorVar.png"
      height=100>


      Drag your documentation scriptable object into the variable
      slot, and the documentation should display on the script itself.


      <img
      src="Assets/ExternalPlugins/EditorDocumentation/Examples/Images/documentationGUIEditing.png"
      height=100>


      <img src="Assets/ExternalPlugins/EditorDocumentation/Examples/Images/documentationGUIDisplaying.png"
      height=500>



      <b><size=30>Happy documenting!</size></b>'
    isEditing: 0
